headline: All It Takes Is $2,000 Invested in Coca-Cola and Each of These 2 High-Yield Dividend Stocks to Help Generate $278 in Passive Income in 2025
summary: The benefits of dividend stocks can be lost by the sound of a roaring market.  Dividends are a way to book a return without selling stock, which can be helpful when equity prices are falling.  Coca-Cola (NYSE: KO), Unilever (NYSE: UL), and LyondellBasell (NYSE: LYB) all have sizable yields.
